rmalized": true, "mention": "COPII", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9968012571334839, "span": {"begin": 396, "end": 401}}, {"id": ["mesh:D013261"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Sterol", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9997164607048035, "span": {"begin": 418, "end": 424}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:7555"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Sterol Regulatory Element Binding Protein", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.99639493227005, "span": {"begin": 418, "end": 459}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:6720"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "SREBPs", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9933711886405945, "span": {"begin": 461, "end": 467}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:51360"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "site-2-protease", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9946091771125793, "span": {"begin": 593, "end": 608}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:51360"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "S2P", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9642024040222168, "span": {"begin": 610, "end": 613}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:6720"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "SREBPs", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.993945300579071, "span": {"begin": 657, "end": 663}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:6721"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "SREBP2", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9892087578773499, "span": {"begin": 745, "end": 751}}, {"id": ["mesh:D002784"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "cholesterol", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9994763731956482, "span": {"begin": 801, "end": 812}}, {"id": ["mesh:D002784"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "cholesterol", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9984922409057617, "span": {"begin": 881, "end": 892}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3638"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "INSIG1", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9591681957244873, "span": {"begin": 901, "end": 907}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:22937"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "SCAP", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9886702299118042, "span": {"begin": 917, "end": 921}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:22937"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "SCAP", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9924502372741699, "span": {"begin": 963, "end": 967}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:26958"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "COPII", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.994268536567688, "span": {"begin": 979, "end": 984}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:6720"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "SREBPs", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9933830499649048, "span": {"begin": 1013, "end": 1019}}, {"id": ["mesh:D002784"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "cholesterol", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9996569156646729, "span": {"begin": 1125, "end": 1136}}], "text": "Insulin-induced gene 1 (INSIG1) is a transmembrane protein in the endoplasmic reticulum membrane (Ouyang et al. 2020). &nbsp;INSIG1 has an important role in lipid synthesis regulation. &nbsp;At low cholesterol levels, INSIG1 has lower binding affinity for SREBP cleavage-activating protein (SCAP), allowing free SCAP to bind to Coat Protein Complex II (COPII; Ouyang et al. 2020). &nbsp;The SCAP-COPII complex enables Sterol Regulatory Element Binding Protein (SREBPs) to move through the endoplasmic reticulum to the Golgi, where membrane-bound transcription factor site-1-protease (S1P) and site-2-protease (S2P) enable proteolytic processing that allows SREBPs to enter the nucleus (Yabe et al. 2002; Yang et al. 2002). &nbsp;In the nucleus, SREBP2 increase gene expression for enzymes involved in cholesterol synthesis (Ouyang et al. 2020; Itkonen et al., 2023). &nbsp;At high cholesterol levels, INSIG1 binds to SCAP, competitively inhibiting the ability of SCAP to bind to COPII (Ouyang et al. 2020). &nbsp;SREBPs are retained in the endoplasmic reticulum rather than being transferred to the Golgi, reducing levels of cholesterol synthesis (Ouyang et al. 2020; Itkonen et al., 2023).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 16:14:15 +0000 2026"}